@{B}@{U}@{JCENTER}HOW TO WRITE AMIGAGUIDE DOCUMENTS

INTRODUCTION@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}
@{"I" LINK "Author"} originally started to write this project some time ago in an endeavour
to teach myself how to write documents in the Amigaguide format.

I had to do this as I could find very little which explained how to do it
properly. 

Although it is not quite complete, I have had a number of requests for it to
be made available so I am now placing it on Aminet as @{"copyrighted" LINK "Copyright"} freeware
or, more accurately, @{"Postcard/E-Mail Ware" LINK "Copyright"11} so that others may benefit from
what has already been completed.

I said above that it is "not quite complete". There are still @{"some points" LINK "AGHTW_Part5/ToDo"}
on which I am unclear. However, having had requests for its release, I did
not want to hold up distribution of it while I searched them out. If anyone
would like to enlighten @{"me" LINK "Author"} then I will update this project and give them
full credit.

I have already had quite a bit of response to and suggestions for this
project and I would like to express my thanks to @{"all those" LINK "Credits"} who have
assisted me in producing "How To Write Amigaguide" versions 1.02 onwards.
As I had hoped, it is becoming an Amiga community project!


@{JCENTER}=== End of Text ===

@ENDNODE

