@{B}@{U}@{JCENTER}HOW TO WRITE AMIGAGUIDE DOCUMENTS

How I Wrote "How To Write Amigaguide Documents"@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}
@{B}"How To Write Amigaguide Documents"@{UB}@{UB} was written on a WB3.1 Amiga 1200
68030/68882 2mb/8mb

It was written with the @{B}EXCELLENT@{UB} shareware program @{B}AMIS@{UB} which, to quote
from the @{B}AMIS@{UB} manual, "is a programme capable of editing multiple file
formats with the power of an unique, easy to use graphical user interface
using normal intuition functions."

I found @{B}AMIS@{UB} on Aminet in the directory "text/edit" and have been using it
to edit my Amigaguide documents ever since.

It is @{B}well worth@{UB} the registration fee.

(Unfortunately I did not find @{B}AMIS@{UB} until I had virtually completed my
@{"other productions" LINK "OtherDocs"}).

@{B}AMIS@{UB} was written by:-

  Willem Mestrom E-mail: wmestrom@cs.ruu.nl or wmestrom@freemail.nl

A visit to the official AMIS home page is worthwhile. It is at:-

  http://people.zeelandnet.nl/supernov/amis.htm


@{JCENTER}=== End of Text ===

