@NODE "History" "How To Write AG - Amigaguide History (BS)"
@TOC "AGHTW_Index/Main"

@{B}@{U}@{JCENTER}HOW TO WRITE AMIGAGUIDE DOCUMENTS

HISTORY@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}
@{B}Version 1.06 12-Feb-98@{UB}

* Added a section on @{"Alternate Way To Reach A Node" LINK "AGHTW_Part5/Alternate"} by double clicking with
  the left mouse button on a word (that is @{B}NOT@{UB} in a link) that is the name
  of the node to be reached.

@{B}Version 1.05 01-Jan-98@{UB}

* Added @{"a section" LINK "AGHTW_Part5/ARexx"} on the use of an ARexx script to open an Amigaguide
  document at a node other than the MAIN node by using the "SHOWNODE"
  function in "amigaguide.library".

@{B}Version 1.04 05-Dec-97@{UB}

* Oh dear oh dear!!!! - found out that Amigaguide/Multiview in Version 39
  will @{"NOT show" LINK "AGHTW_Part1/Important"31} lines which have this sequence of characters:-

     a backslash
     the \@ symbol
     any character immediately after the \@ other than space or {

  so users of version 39 had a lot of blank lines while reading this
  project!!! (@{B}VERY @{UB}strange as versions 34 and 40 @{B}DO @{UB}show such lines!!!).

  Completely rewrote the whole think to fix this.

* As I have now been able to access a version 39 setup I have revised all
  sections where there was doubt expressed as to how version 39 reacted. 

* My thanks to @{"Chris Freestone" LINK "Credits"20} for all his help in the above two matters.

* I found out that there is a @{"problem with `Retrace'" LINK "Using"86} with links to lines in
  the same node when using version 39. I have therefore created a lot more
  nodes rather than having links to lines other than the first in the node.

* Added the section on the @{"BEEP" LINK "AGHTW_Part2/Beep"} section. (Thanks to @{"Oleg Sergeev" LINK "Credits"27}.)

* Added a bit to the @{"Unrecognised Commands" LINK "AGHTW_Part1/Unrecognised"} to explain what happens when the
  unrecognised command is @{"set up similarly to link commands" LINK "AGHTW_Part1/Unrecognised"37}.

* Added section on @{"Current Directory" LINK "AGHTW_Part1/CD"} recognised by Amigaguide/Multiview.

* Transferred section on @{"Links to Non Amigaguide Documents" LINK "AGHTW_Part2/NonGuideDocs"} from the node
  @{"Links To Document Nodes" LINK "AGHTW_Part2/LinkCommand"} to its own node.

* Added section on the @{"debugging feature" LINK "AGHTW_Part5/Debugging"} (thanks to @{"Richard Burke" LINK "AGHTW_Boring_Stuff/Credits"40} for the
  information) which resulted in a slight change to the @{"DATABASE" LINK "AGHTW_Part1/Database"18} section.

* Rewrote @{"Problem 7" LINK "AGHTW_Part5/Problems"147} when I found that versions 34 and 39 did @{B}not@{UB} react in
  the same way as I had previously thought they did.

* A @{B}LOT@{UB} of other minor cosmetic changes that have made no real change to the
  context. These are too numerous to mention.

@{B}Version 1.03 26-Sep-97@{UB}

* Whoops - Forggot to speell chek!!!! - Sory about that fokes!!
  No other changes.

@{B}Version 1.02 21-Sep-97@{UB}

* Project became far too large for a single document so I split it into 7
  different disk files. (This, in itself, did not cause any changes in
  context.)

* Rewrote @{"NEXT & PREV" LINK "AGHTW_Part3/NextPrev"} section to explain how I included these commands
  in the first and last nodes of each section to link them all together
  after splitting the project into 7 disk files.

* Included @{"Links To Other File Types in Early Amigaguide Versions" LINK "AGHTW_Part2/OtherLinksEarly"}.
  (Thanks to @{"Christopher Jeffery" LINK "Credits"5})

* Following on the above additions, the @{"SYSTEM" LINK "AGHTW_Part2/System"} command section has been
  completely rewritten in order to:-
    - emphasise that @{"any program" LINK "AGHTW_Part2/System"15}, not just AmigaDOS commands, can be used
      in the SYSTEM argument, and
    - include section on advantages of @{"using RUN" LINK "AGHTW_Part2/SystemRun"} in the SYSTEM argument,
    - and generally tidy it up.

* Included note on @{"problem with macros" LINK "AGHTW_Part3/Macros"133} that include long strings.
  (Thanks to  @{"Michael Schulz" LINK "Credits"13})

* Rewrote @{"TOC" LINK "AGHTW_Part3/Toc"} section without making any changes to context.

* Included a section on the @{"MAIN Node" LINK "AGHTW_Part1/MainNode"}.

* Added a @{"section" LINK "AGHTW_Part3/WinSize"28} to the "Window Size" node to discuss a method of
  obtaining a display window size and position other than the default or
  that saved to the Envarc:Amigaguide/ or Envarc:Multiview/ directories by
  use of the menu item "Setting/Save As Defaults".

@{B}Version 1.01@{UB} - First public release on Aminet


@{JCENTER}=== End of Text ===










































